div.p:
When therefore thou wilt offer vp thy selfe to God, first


looke vpon Christ our Lord, how at this day he offers vp himselfe in the aforesaid maner, and make thy offering in the vertue, and vnion of his; or rather make that very selfe same offering of Christ, wherin he included thine. And more then this, let this thy offe ring be without proprietie, or any part of thy owne interest, not respecting, either earthly or heauēly goods, but the pure wil of God, and diuine prouidence, vnto the which thou oughtest to submit thy will, and to sacrifice thy selfe a perpetual holocaust, & thus for getting euery creature, thou shalt say, behold my Sauior and Creator, a peece of clay in the hand of thy diuine prouidence;


make of mee that which seemeth best to thee: and pleaseth thee in life, in death, and after death, as well in time, as in eternitie.
